# Purpose: Add mailing list headers on outbound mail.
# These headers help mail clients recognize this as a legitimate
# mailing list and can improve spam filtering scores.

# ============================================================
# LIST HEADERS (RFC 2369)
# ============================================================
# These headers identify this as a proper mailing list.
# Gmail and other providers look for these to classify mail.

# Add List-Id header for mailing list identification
/^From:.*@ssc\.manage2soar\.com/
    PREPEND List-Id: SSC Members <members.ssc.manage2soar.com>

# Add List-Post header (where to send messages to the list)
# Mail clients use this for "Reply to List" functionality
/^From:.*@ssc\.manage2soar\.com/
    PREPEND List-Post: <mailto:members@ssc.manage2soar.com>

# Note: We intentionally do NOT set Reply-To header.
# The List-Post header above enables mail client "Reply to List" buttons,
# while allowing recipients to reply privately to the sender if desired.

# Add Precedence header (helps spam filters recognize bulk mail)
/^From:.*@ssc\.manage2soar\.com/
    PREPEND Precedence: list
